Interface Flowchart.EdgeConsumer

  • Enclosing class:
    Flowchart
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface Flowchart.EdgeConsumer
    A functional interface to describe the action to be taken for each edge in a graph search of the flowchart.
    Author:
    rongomai
    See Also:
    Flowchart.doSearch(Predicate, EdgeConsumer), Flowchart.doSearch(EdgeConsumer)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void accept(Node node, Node next, Outcome outcome)
      Performs an operation on an edge of the flowchart.

    • Method Detail

      • accept

        void accept(Node node,
            Node next,
            Outcome outcome)
        Performs an operation on an edge of the flowchart.
        Parameters:
        node - the "from" node of the edge. This will be set to null to indicate the first node of the search.
        next - the "to" node of the edge. This will be the first node of the search when node is set to null.
        outcome - the value of the edge.
